In a cloud environment, you end up having multiple parties involved: the cluster administrator and
the application developer. The role of the cluster administrator is to be able to provision
resources, monitor the cluster state and take care of incidents.

The application developer on the other hand, only cares about having a message propagate from one
system to another, and the messaging service is a way to do that.

